# Prime Intellect GPU availability watch list.
#
# Format:  <gpu_type>  <min>  <max>  [socket]
#  - gpu_type must match the API's `gpuType` value exactly (case-sensitive).
#  - min/max are inclusive bounds on the offer's gpuCount.
#    Use min == max to require an exact count (e.g. exactly 8 GPUs).
#  - socket is optional: PCIe or SXM.
#  - "#" comments and blank lines are ignored.
#
# Real `gpuType` values seen in the wild include:
#   H100_80GB, H200_141GB, B300_262GB,
#   A100_80GB, A100_40GB, A6000_48GB, A40_48GB, A10_24GB,
#   L4_24GB, RTX4090_24GB, RTX3090_24GB, RTX_PRO_6000B_96GB.

H100_80GB     8   8
H200_141GB    4   8
A100_80GB     1   8
# B300_262GB  4   8   SXM
